ar the soul inside out'Sara Niles, Torn From the Inside Out\n\n- Sara Niles, Torn From The Inside Out\n|\nWhen I write sometimes I strike gold, sometimes I labor in vain and keep producing rubbish\n\n- Bangambiki Habyarimana, Pearls Of Eternity\n|\nOnce I knew the depth where no hope was, and darkness lay on the face of all things. Then love came and set my soul free.\n\n- Helen Keller, Optimism\n|\nI will not stand here to be insulted by you, hedgepig,' Mangiz fumed.'Then stand somewhere else and I'll insult you there, featherbag!!\n\n- Brian Jacques, Mattimeo\n|\nBut the fruit of the Spirit is love, joy, peace, patience, kindness, goodness, faithfulness, gentleness, self-control; against such things there is no law.\n\n- Galatians\n|\nWhat could be more beautiful than a dear old lady growing wise with age? Every age can be enchanting, provided you live within it.\n\n- Brigitte\n|\nIf you are to suppose that natural reasons are the cause of everything, then it can only lead to the conclusion that consciousness is an illusion.\n\n- Lewis N. Roe, From A To Theta: Taking The Tricky Subject Of Religion And Explaining Why It Makes Sense In A Way We Can All Understand\n|\nNext time I will ...''From now on I will ...'- What makes me think I am wiser today than I will be tomorrow?\n\n- Hugh Prather, Notes to Myself: My Struggle to Become a Person\n|\nSo they're looking for a new face, with a voice to go along. I can tell you right now that ain't my style. I don't do no sing alongs, with my freedom.\n\n- Tegan\n|\nWhen two people got cross with each other and stop talking, the deep silence in the air will continue to speak glowingly!\n\n- Mehmet\n|\nIf you conform, you miss all of the adventures and stand against the progress of society.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nOur friend Chewy doesn’t speak much, but he chews a lot of tobacco so we call him Chewbacco.\n\n- Michael Diack, The Super Spud Trilogy\n|\nA friend recently shared that even if he is in a rough mood, when someone smiles a