ld will take you the same.\n\n- Irish\n|\nSilence, when correctly timed, can speak multitudes of words to a person, without any extra effort on your part.\n\n- Innocent Mwatsikesimbe, Mirror\n|\nPeople always knock what's new but I love the modern Internet, where cleverness is currency. Social media is a cleverness meritocracy. We're living in it.\n\n- Alexei\n|\nI think part of me doesn't want to remember him, for fear of missing him too much.\n\n- Francesca Marciano, Casa Rossa\n|\nIf you want to get wealth, focus on wealth. If you want happiness, focus on happiness.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nA permanent pathThat, once illuminated,Goes ever onward – a way home…\n\n- Scott\n|\nI will build the best Potemkin village for you, my love!\n\n- Ljupka Cvetanova, The New Land\n|\nHeroin was a coping mechanism that I had used to deal with my underlying fears. They were the real problems; heroin wasn't the culprit, my fears were.\n\n- Pax Prentiss, The Alcoholism and Addiction Cure\n|\nHappily ever after?' 'If justice doesn't triumph and love doesn't make the circle in entertainment fiction, what's the point? Real life sucks too often.\n\n- Nora Roberts, Angels Fall\n|\nIf there is only nothingness after death, what’s the point of this world?\n\n- Fuminori Nakamura, The Kingdom\n|\nAnd here's something else I learned: you lose some people that way - fast and blinding. But some people inch away from you slowly, in barely discernible steps.\n\n- Lauren\n|\nYes, you can make a difference! You can speak on behalf of those who are voiceless.\n\n- E.N. Supen, Turning Point\n|\nMy dad was diagnosed with cancer, so we ended up burying him a year to the day that he was diagnosed.\n\n- Seann\n|\nPride, envy, avarice - these are the sparks have set on fire the hearts of all men.\n\n- Dante\n|\nIf we deny the thirst of love, we stand to lose the last known address of the stranger whithin us.\n\n- Sorin\n|\nI climb mountains, while you keep sinking in sand.\n\n- Jenna\n|\n... A man's wife can hold him devilish uneasy, if she begins to scold and fret, and perplex him, at a time when he has a full load for a railroad car on his mind already.\n\n- David\n|\nLike hatred, guilt can’t be locked in the silence of forgetting, without taking part of your soul with it.\n\n- Shannon\n|\nNow is the time to ask yourself, what you believe.\n\n- Rob MacGregor, Indiana Jones and the Last Crusade\n|\nJedi are conversationalists and negotiators, bringing people together and solving problems. Jedi listen and feel to what others are saying.\n\n- Stephen Richards, Develop Jedi Self-Confidence: Unleash the Force within You\n|\nGod is love, and he who abides in love abides in God, and God in him.\n\n- Anonymous, Holy Bible: King James Version\n|\nEven after such milestones as Kathryn Bigelow winning an Oscar, there still seem to be few women in leadership roles.\n\n- Julia\n|\nHe pointed the scepter around the library and had an instant input of all of the books that were there into his brain, as if he had read them all at once.\n\n- Kaza Kingsley, The Secret of Ashona\n|\nThe glory of fame isn't in having so many people know you, but in having so many people know you care. Otherwise, it's like being drawn to a fire to find no warmth.\n\n- Richelle E. Goodrich, Smile Anyway\n|\nHumans are easy to read, because what they’re not saying speaks volumes.\n\n- Joel\n|\nI am always doing what I thought I couldn't do, because I might learn something. Henri Marcel - Marriage a Journey and A Dog\n\n- Brenda\n|\nI think what is important for things to be funny is if you the listener, or the reader, get a chance to supply the humor of it yourself.\n\n- Ian\n|\nEven if your world seems to be falling apart, you can be confident in that you are in His hand of grace.\n\n- Sunday\n|\nI'd always rather be working - and you know what? My kids would rather me be working. If I stay at home, I'll only buy another car or spend their money.\n\n- Danny\n|\nSpeaking felt impossible, as contained and enclosed as she was, a longing that went on a loop, a longing for nothing at all.\n\n- Catherine Lacey, The Answers\n|\nWe are not afraid of rivalry, for we are unique\n\n- Sunday\n|\nThe destiny of a man is determined by his daily action, God won't allow you go anywhere, if you don't make an attempt to move.\n\n- Michael\n|\nOne faith, one family.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nWe see only half , yet speak like we know the other .\n\n- Beven\n|\nThey thrived on the rapid turnover of acquaintances, the lack of involvement with others, and the total self-sufficiency of lives which, needing nothing, were never dissapointed.\n\n- J.G. Ballard, High-Rise\n|\nThere's always a learning curve, where you've got to learn what your subject is all about.\n\n- Brad\n|\nWith limited money you can survive, with more money you can live.\n\n- Amit\n|\nYou,” I said, “are sweet music in a distant room.\n\n- Patrick Rothfuss, The Wise Man's Fear\n|\nA reader lives a thousand lives before he dies, said Jojen. The man who never reads lives only one.\n\n- George R.R. Martin, A Dance with Dragons\n|\nAnd in the absence of facts, myth rushes in, the kudzu of history.\n\n- Stacy Schiff, Cleopatra: A Life\n|\nThere are plenty of other ways to mend a broken heart, and doing some list full of stuff that you don't want to do doesn't have to be one of them.\n\n- Anna Bell, The Bucket List to Mend a Broken Heart\n|\nMan is constantly being assured today that he has more power than ever before in history, but his daily experience is one of powerlessness.\n\n- Richard M. Weaver, Ideas Have Consequences\n|\nBut women have lust, too. Why should they be relegated to the position of custodian of emotions, watcher of the infants, feeder of the soul, body and pride of man?\n\n- Sylvia Plath, The Unabridged Journals of Sylvia Plath\n|\nFar, far below the deepest delvings of the dwarves, the world is gnawed by nameless things.\n\n- J.R.R.\n|\nIf your financial life is not in order, every other area of your life will be in di